  "issue_title": "Bump bittensor stack to 10.3.1 and drop substrate-interface",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\nBump `bittensor` to 10.3.1, `bittensor-cli` to 9.21.1, `bittensor-wallet` to 4.0.1, and drop the direct `substrate-interface` dependency. The new bittensor stack already ships `async_substrate_interface`, so `substrate-interface` is redundant and can be removed from `pyproject.toml`.\n\n## Motivation\n\n- `bittensor 10.0.1` is ~3 minor versions behind upstream (10.3.1 is current). Staying on 10.0.x leaves us out of fixes and exposes us to the `substrate-interface` package, which upstream bittensor has migrated off of in favor of `async_substrate_interface`\n- Two parallel substrate clients (`substrateinterface.SubstrateInterface` and `async_substrate_interface.SubstrateInterface`) are imported across `gittensor/cli/issue_commands/` and `gittensor/validator/issue_competitions/`. They expose the same API surface for our use, so keeping both is dead weight",
